From: Stephen Wheet <stephen@wheet>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: bcm2712-rpi-cm5: Trust hardware card-detect on sdio1

The BCM2712 SDHCI controller exposes a working SDHCI_CARD_PRESENT bit
in its PRESENT_STATE register and raises SDHCI_INT_CARD_INSERT/REMOVE
on physical state changes. On carriers that route the microSD slot's
card-detect line to the controller's native CD pin (CM4IO, CM5IO,
DeskPi Super6C, and the upstream RPi CM4/CM5 IO board reference
designs), broken-cd is unnecessary.

With broken-cd set, drivers/mmc/core/host.c sets MMC_CAP_NEEDS_POLL,
which prevents mmc_rescan() from short-circuiting when the slot is
empty. The kernel then issues CMD52 (SDIO probe) into the empty slot,
which never completes, and sdhci_timeout_timer() emits

  mmc0: Timeout waiting for hardware cmd interrupt.
  ============ SDHCI REGISTER DUMP ===========

every ~10 seconds for the lifetime of the system.

Drop broken-cd. The controller's native card-detect handles both
empty-slot quiet and hot-insert via SDHCI_INT_CARD_INSERT.

CARRIER COMPATIBILITY: This change assumes the carrier wires microSD
CD to the BCM2712 native CD pin. Verified on: CM4IO, CM5IO, DeskPi
Super6C. Carriers that route CD to a GPIO instead must use
cd-gpios = <...>; in addition to dropping broken-cd. Carriers that
don't wire CD at all must keep broken-cd or set non-removable +
cd-gpios with a tied-low GPIO; this patch will produce
"card never detected" on such hardware.

Note: this patch is generated against the post-0006 tree (after
0006-0001-ARM-dts-bcm2712-Slow-down-eMMC-interface.patch has removed
mmc-hs400-1_8v, mmc-hs400-enhanced-strobe, and supports-cqe = <1>
from this same node). bldr applies overlay patches alphabetically,
so 0011- lands after 0006- with no collision.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-cm5.dtsi | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-cm5.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-cm5.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-cm5.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712-rpi-cm5.dtsi
@@ -291,7 +291,6 @@
 	sd-uhs-ddr50;
 	sd-uhs-sdr104;
 	mmc-hs200-1_8v;
-	broken-cd;
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
